http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Chevireddy-held-in-Samaikyandhra-stir-case/article14006431.ece

The Tirupati Railway Police on Monday arrested Chandragiri Legislator Chevireddy Bhaskar Reddy in connection with a Samaikhyandhra Agitation case, which was registered in 2009.Mr. Bhaskar Reddy, who had been served a non-bailable warrant, was produced before the Special Judicial First Class Magistrate for Railways, Nellore, and was remanded till January 29. He was shifted to the Nellore Central Jail.According to sources, more than 500 agitators, including Mr. Bhaskar Reddy, had entered the Tirupati railway station on December 11, 2009, in a bid to hold ‘rail roko’ as part of the Samaikhyandhra agitation.They were accused of “trespassing” and squatting on the second track between platforms No. 1 and 2, thereby delaying the Sapthagiri Express (Train No. 6054) for more than half-an-hour.A case (Crime No. 933/2009) was registered against him under Sections 147 and 174 (a) of the Railway Act.After preliminary enquiries, a complaint was filed in the court of the Special Judicial First Class Magistrate for Railways, Nellore, on September 10, 2012.A non-bailable warrant was issued against Mr. Bhaskar Reddy on September 28, 2015, as he did not attend court proceedings on the same day. Mr. Bhaskar Reddy (A3) is the third accused in the case.